# Cloudflare Pages _redirects — SPA client-side routing fallback.
#
# Every unknown path returns 200 + index.html so the SvelteKit router
# resolves the route on the client. Without this, navigating directly to
# `/brief/2026-05-24` would return Pages' default 404 because the static
# build has no per-route HTML files (adapter-static `fallback: 'index.html'`
# only handles unmatched routes during build, not at deploy-time fetch).
#
# The API is reached cross-origin via VITE_API_BASE (set in CF Pages
# project env vars). Proxying /api/* through Pages was the alternative —
# rejected because it adds ~30 ms latency per request and hides CORS
# behaviour. See apps/web/README.md for the deploy topology.
#
# NOTE on stale-chunk recovery: do NOT try to exclude `/_app/*` here
# with a `… 404` rule. CF Pages processes _redirects before checking
# asset existence, so a status-404 rule whose destination is missing
# falls through to the SPA fallback — verified empirically in PR #285
# and the hotfix attempt #286, neither of which prevented the
# blank-screen bug. The canonical fix lives in the SvelteKit config:
# `kit.version.pollInterval` + `data-sveltekit-reload` on the layout
# wrapper. See svelte.config.js + src/routes/+layout.svelte and the
# memory note `reference_cf_pages_redirects_no_404_for_missing_file`.
